  <div id="page-content">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div id="header-container"></div>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <main class="page-ilae_classification">
      <h2 class="page-title">ILAE Classification of the Epilepsies</h2>
      <!-- Tab Buttons -->
      <div class="tab-buttons">
        <button id="classification-tab-btn" class="active" onclick="showILaeTab('classification')">Seizure Classification</button>
        <button id="syndromes-tab-btn" onclick="showILaeTab('syndromes')">Epilepsy Syndromes</button>
      </div>
      <!-- Seizure Classification Content -->
      <div id="classification-tab" class="ilae-tab-content">
        <div class="intro-text">
          <p>The updated ILAE classification of epileptic seizures (2025) categorizes seizures based on their onset with the new distinction of preserved versus impaired consciousness (no longer using "awareness"). For full guidelines, refer to the <a href="https://www.ilae.org/files/dmfile/updated-classification-of-epileptic-seizures-2025.pdf" target="_blank">2025 ILAE Classification of Epileptic Seizures PDF</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Classification diagram -->
        <div class="classification-diagram">
          <div class="classification-header">
            <h3>2025 ILAE Seizure Classification Framework</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="classification-container">
            <div class="classification-column">
              <div class="classification-type focal">
                <h4>Focal Onset</h4>
                <p>Seizures originating within networks limited to one hemisphere</p>
                <div class="classification-subtypes">
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>With Preserved Consciousness</h5>
                    <p>Patient maintains awareness of self and environment</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Motor onset (e.g., tonic, clonic, myoclonic)</li>
                      <li>Non-motor onset (e.g., sensory, cognitive, emotional)</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>With Impaired Consciousness</h5>
                    <p>Patient has altered awareness of self and environment</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Motor manifestations may occur</li>
                      <li>Automatisms may be present</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Focal to Bilateral Tonic-Clonic</h5>
                    <p>Begins focally and evolves to engage both hemispheres</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="classification-column">
              <div class="classification-type generalized">
                <h4>Generalized Onset</h4>
                <p>Seizures originating within and rapidly engaging bilateral networks</p>
                <div class="classification-subtypes">
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Motor</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Tonic-clonic</li>
                      <li>Clonic</li>
                      <li>Tonic</li>
                      <li>Myoclonic</li>
                      <li>Myoclonic-tonic-clonic</li>
                      <li>Myoclonic-atonic</li>
                      <li>Atonic</li>
                      <li>Epileptic spasms</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Non-Motor (Absence)</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Typical</li>
                      <li>Atypical</li>
                      <li>Myoclonic</li>
                      <li>Eyelid myoclonia</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="classification-column">
              <div class="classification-type unknown">
                <h4>Unknown Onset</h4>
                <p>When the onset is not clearly determined</p>
                <div class="classification-subtypes">
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Motor</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Tonic-clonic</li>
                      <li>Epileptic spasms</li>
                      <li>Other motor</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Non-Motor</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Behavior arrest</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="subtype-card">
                    <h5>Unclassified</h5>
                    <p>Insufficient information or unable to place in other categories</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Changes in 2025 Classification -->
        <div class="key-changes-section">
          <h3>Key Changes in the 2025 Classification</h3>
          <div class="changes-grid">
            <div class="change-card">
              <div class="change-icon"><i class="fas fa-brain"></i></div>
              <h4>Consciousness vs. Awareness</h4>
              <p>The term "awareness" has been replaced with "consciousness" to better reflect the patient's state during seizures.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="change-card">
              <div class="change-icon"><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i></div>
              <h4>Network Emphasis</h4>
              <p>Greater focus on identifying the networks involved rather than just the clinical manifestations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="change-card">
              <div class="change-icon"><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i></div>
              <h4>Refinement of Motor Subtypes</h4>
              <p>More precise definitions of motor seizure subtypes with standardized terminology.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="change-card">
              <div class="change-icon"><i class="fas fa-stethoscope"></i></div>
              <h4>Clinical Utility</h4>
              <p>Classification designed to be more practical for clinical diagnosis and treatment planning.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

